1
00:00:00,310 --> 00:00:02,040
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,110 --> 00:00:03,540
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:21,730 --> 00:00:22,890
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

4
00:00:22,890 --> 00:00:24,800
(Episode 20)

5
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:26,360
Did you forget something?

6
00:00:27,170 --> 00:00:28,830
Wait, you're sleeping here?

7
00:00:29,630 --> 00:00:31,100
How did you know?

8
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:36,010
I told him. Why did you run ahead?
I told you to wait up.

9
00:00:36,170 --> 00:00:39,340
What were you thinking?
Leaving the door unlocked like that?

10
00:00:41,210 --> 00:00:43,780
I was just going to read this,
then lock up.

11
00:00:44,450 --> 00:00:46,920
Whatever. Get up.
You're coming to my place.

12
00:00:47,120 --> 00:00:50,860
No, really.
I'm more comfortable sleeping here.

13
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:53,860
Stop being stubborn
and pack your things.

14
00:00:53,930 --> 00:00:58,200
- Seriously, I said I'm fine.
- So when did you two get so close?

15
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:01,770
Oh, we dropped formalities
over drinks.

16
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:03,230
Turns out she's younger than me.

17
00:01:03,370 --> 00:01:04,740
I see.

18
00:01:05,300 --> 00:01:08,010
Anyway, let's get going.
My aunt told me to bring you over.

19
00:01:08,070 --> 00:01:11,840
If you don't listen,
I'll tell my aunt to fire you.

20
00:01:11,980 --> 00:01:14,180
Gosh, that's a low blow.

21
00:01:15,180 --> 00:01:16,180
Let's go.

22
00:01:16,510 --> 00:01:18,420
Some stuff happened in the area,
so we're worried.

23
00:01:18,950 --> 00:01:19,950
Something happened?

24
00:01:20,490 --> 00:01:21,820
What was it?

25
00:01:24,190 --> 00:01:25,960
- Over here! Here!
- Hey, Officer, over here!

26
00:01:26,060 --> 00:01:28,660
- Here!
- Get out of the way! Darn it!

27
00:01:28,730 --> 00:01:30,260
No!

28
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:41,540
Darn it!

29
00:01:44,180 --> 00:01:45,540
Hey! No!

30
00:01:46,180 --> 00:01:49,610
Hey, Dong Ik! Hey!

31
00:01:49,750 --> 00:01:54,150
Dong Ik! Stay with me! Dong Ik!

32
00:01:54,750 --> 00:01:58,960
Dong Ik! Don't move! Stay still.

33
00:01:59,020 --> 00:02:01,090
Hey. Oh, no.

34
00:02:01,090 --> 00:02:03,260
Hey, you... Are you okay?

35
00:02:03,630 --> 00:02:06,970
I'm okay.
I think it's just a little sting.

36
00:02:07,070 --> 00:02:10,500
- Are you sure you're okay?
- Yes, I told you I am.

37
00:02:10,570 --> 00:02:11,940
My goodness.

38
00:02:13,510 --> 00:02:15,810
What's going on? Is he hurt?

39
00:02:16,310 --> 00:02:19,480
The suspect! He went that way!
Quick!

40
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:21,110
Hey! Stay with me.

41
00:02:21,950 --> 00:02:22,950
Darn it...

42
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:27,290
Let me go!

43
00:02:30,020 --> 00:02:33,490
- Darn it. Hey, let me go!
- You jerk!

44
00:02:36,690 --> 00:02:39,330
You're under arrest
for aggravated robbery.

45
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:42,070
You have the right to an attorney
and to make a statement.

46
00:02:42,370 --> 00:02:45,140
You have the right to remain silent
and to contest your arrest.

47
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:47,540
- Understand?
- Darn it.

48
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,540
You little...

49
00:02:54,150 --> 00:02:58,780
Gosh, what do we do? Darn it...
Hey! Can you get up?

50
00:02:58,850 --> 00:03:01,690
Yes, I told you I'm fine.
It was just a little sting.

51
00:03:01,750 --> 00:03:05,020
Goodness. What are we going to do?
Oh, man.

52
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:09,290
- What happened? Did you get him?
- Yes. What about you two?

53
00:03:09,290 --> 00:03:11,060
- Are you okay?
- Dr. Gong!

54
00:03:11,660 --> 00:03:14,400
Hey! Are you okay?
You're not hurt, are you?

55
00:03:14,470 --> 00:03:16,630
Why are you here? It's dangerous.
I told you to stay in the clinic.

56
00:03:16,700 --> 00:03:19,970
- Dr. Yang, are you hurt?
- Oh, no, I'm fine. Nothing serious.

57
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:23,370
What do you mean, "fine?" Come on.
Let's go to the clinic and treat it.

58
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:27,850
- Officer Jung, are you okay?
- Yes, just a scratch. I'm fine.

59
00:03:28,050 --> 00:03:31,880
No, really. Officer Jung,
you should get that cleaned up too.

60
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:34,590
No, that's okay.
I just needed to see you were okay.

61
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:35,950
I should be on my way.

62
00:03:36,650 --> 00:03:39,290
- But it'll only take a second.
- It's fine. You've had it rough.

63
00:03:40,530 --> 00:03:44,460
Come on, let's hurry up and go.
Get a move on!

64
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,630
Nurse Oh, I'm sorry.

65
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:50,670
I shouldn't have called Dr. Gong.
I bet you were really scared.

66
00:03:51,270 --> 00:03:53,500
I was a little startled,
but I'm okay.

67
00:03:54,170 --> 00:03:55,570
Will he be okay without stitches?

68
00:03:55,870 --> 00:03:57,840
Yes, it's a superficial cut.

69
00:03:58,640 --> 00:03:59,740
But man, seriously...

70
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,780
Hey, you could have been
seriously hurt.

71
00:04:02,850 --> 00:04:04,480
Yes, tell me about it.

72
00:04:05,220 --> 00:04:08,320
Wow, I guess
this coat saved my life.

73
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:14,630
Hey, but what made you think
to take a knife for me?

74
00:04:15,090 --> 00:04:17,360
Oh, it was... I don't know.
It was just instinct.

75
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:22,130
Because it would hurt me more
to see you get hurt.

76
00:04:22,770 --> 00:04:23,770
My gosh.

77
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:25,870
This guy, seriously.

78
00:04:30,010 --> 00:04:33,240
Still, why is a young woman
sleeping at a restaurant?

79
00:04:33,980 --> 00:04:35,510
Apparently, she's from the US.

80
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:38,420
I don't know the details either.
I'll ask her when she gets here.

81
00:04:38,950 --> 00:04:42,050
- Mom! Auntie.
- Hey! Why are you by yourself?

82
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:44,190
Hey! What are you doing?
Get in here.

83
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:50,030
Hello.
I'm sorry for coming by so late.

84
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:54,670
I really feel bad about this.
I'll just go sleep at a 24-hour spa.

85
00:04:54,970 --> 00:04:58,800
Nonsense. I'm the one
who told her to bring you over.

86
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:01,570
Come on, say hello.
This is Eun Bin's mom.

87
00:05:02,340 --> 00:05:03,570
Hello.

88
00:05:04,710 --> 00:05:07,510
- What?
- It's you, right? That little brat.

89
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:08,910
That weird woman...

90
00:05:11,250 --> 00:05:12,780
You two know each other?

91
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:14,390
What? How?

92
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:16,550
Wow, that's wild.

93
00:05:16,850 --> 00:05:19,490
- It's just that...
- It's nothing, really.

94
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:21,560
It's late.
You should go up and rest.

95
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:23,700
Right. Let's head on up.

96
00:05:25,330 --> 00:05:27,870
Thank you for letting me stay,
just for tonight.

97
00:05:28,170 --> 00:05:29,430
Okay, this way.

98
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:35,870
Gosh, and he hasn't even called.

99
00:05:36,710 --> 00:05:37,940
I wonder what's going on.

100
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:40,780
- Hey, take it easy. Walk slowly.
- I'm okay.

101
00:05:40,850 --> 00:05:43,450
- Hey, man. We're here.
- Okay.

102
00:05:43,450 --> 00:05:44,780
Honey.

103
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:48,520
My goodness, what happened?
Are you hurt?

104
00:05:48,590 --> 00:05:50,350
It's just a little something.

105
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:54,290
There was an incident at the market.

106
00:05:54,790 --> 00:05:55,860
What kind of incident?

107
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:59,330
A robber came charging at me.

108
00:05:59,630 --> 00:06:03,970
Dong Ik jumped in to block him
and got grazed by the knife.

109
00:06:03,970 --> 00:06:05,740
A knife...

110
00:06:06,140 --> 00:06:10,480
- A knife?
- It's okay, honey. Just a scratch.

111
00:06:11,110 --> 00:06:12,680
Where? Let me see. Where is it?

112
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:17,780
Look, Jeong Han gave me first aid.
Don't worry.

113
00:06:18,980 --> 00:06:22,020
He got hurt because of me.
I'm so sorry.

114
00:06:22,420 --> 00:06:25,620
Hey, stop being so dramatic
and get going, okay?

115
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:29,660
Yes, okay. Hey,
you can't let this get infected,

116
00:06:29,830 --> 00:06:31,630
so be really careful to keep it dry.
Got it?

117
00:06:31,630 --> 00:06:33,260
Okay, got it.

118
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,470
- See you.
- Yes...

119
00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:37,770
Again, I'm so sorry about this.

120
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:41,770
- Take it easy. All right.
- Yes. Don't worry.

121
00:06:42,270 --> 00:06:43,370
Let me see.

122
00:06:43,370 --> 00:06:44,810
- I'm fine.
- You're bleeding.

123
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:47,110
I'm fine. He patched it up well.

124
00:06:49,150 --> 00:06:52,220
Honestly, what is all this?

125
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:54,290
Shouldn't we go to a proper hospital
or something, honey?

126
00:06:54,290 --> 00:06:57,050
No. I told you, I'm fine.

127
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:59,420
But honey, more importantly,

128
00:07:00,090 --> 00:07:01,090
what am I going to do?

129
00:07:01,730 --> 00:07:02,730
What is it?

130
00:07:03,630 --> 00:07:05,830
I didn't get to tell Jeong Han.

131
00:07:09,970 --> 00:07:13,200
Since Hyun Bin said
he'd tell Gong Ju Ah,

132
00:07:13,740 --> 00:07:15,410
he'll probably find out
when he gets home.

133
00:07:22,850 --> 00:07:24,750
Seong Mi, I got this.

134
00:07:25,420 --> 00:07:27,690
Between patients, filming your show,
and even modeling,

135
00:07:28,250 --> 00:07:30,620
you're overdoing it these days.
You should go get some rest.

136
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:34,390
He's right. You have to be up early
for work tomorrow.

137
00:07:34,460 --> 00:07:35,560
Go on, rest. Okay?

138
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:37,360
This is how I relax.

139
00:07:37,860 --> 00:07:40,600
Having stable interactions
with my family...

140
00:07:40,870 --> 00:07:45,470
calms the brain's stress response
and balances the nervous system.

141
00:07:45,670 --> 00:07:48,640
So it's about relaxing your mind,
not your body.

142
00:07:48,740 --> 00:07:50,110
Exactly, Mother.

143
00:07:51,010 --> 00:07:52,710
Anyway, I wonder
why Jeong Han is so late.

144
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:56,850
He's likely hanging out with Bucket
after his late shift.

145
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:58,520
Just the two of them. Oh, brother.

146
00:08:00,450 --> 00:08:03,720
That reminds me.
I went to Ju Ah's office earlier,

147
00:08:03,890 --> 00:08:06,960
- and I ran into Bucket's wife.
- At her office?

148
00:08:07,890 --> 00:08:10,230
- I'm home.
- You're back.

149
00:08:10,290 --> 00:08:14,330
- Ju Ah. Hey, have you had dinner?
- Yes. I'm going upstairs to rest.

150
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:18,770
- Okay.
- So you met Dr. Yang's wife?

151
00:08:19,070 --> 00:08:21,710
Guess what?
She was trying to give the VP...

152
00:08:21,710 --> 00:08:24,010
homemade ginseng chicken soup.

153
00:08:24,710 --> 00:08:27,880
For Taehan's sick chairman
in the hospital.

154
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:28,950
Oh, my.

155
00:08:29,010 --> 00:08:32,680
- Wow, that's laying it on thick.
- I know, right?

156
00:08:33,050 --> 00:08:35,420
- I tried to stop her. Guess what?
- What happened?

157
00:08:35,420 --> 00:08:38,720
- She actually listened to me.
- Oh, my, really?

158
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,120
Hey, Ju Ah!

159
00:08:40,390 --> 00:08:41,860
What are you doing
just standing there?

160
00:08:42,390 --> 00:08:46,230
- Oh, where's Dad?
- He's not back yet. Why do you ask?

161
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:48,200
No, it's nothing...

162
00:08:53,100 --> 00:08:54,110
(Breadcrumbs)

163
00:09:03,950 --> 00:09:05,880
I was going to make you
some Argentinian food.

164
00:09:06,950 --> 00:09:08,950
I was waiting
to surprise you with it,

165
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:12,790
but then your mother
came in, so I hid.

166
00:09:18,030 --> 00:09:20,730
Looks like nobody knows yet.

167
00:09:21,830 --> 00:09:25,540
They'll flip out if they find out.
What am I going to do?

168
00:09:30,780 --> 00:09:31,780
Yes.

169
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:35,110
You sure you won't be uncomfortable?

170
00:09:37,250 --> 00:09:40,620
You have such a kind heart,
Eun Bin. Yes.

171
00:09:41,450 --> 00:09:43,090
Get some sleep. I'm hanging up.

172
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:47,960
Oh, boy...

173
00:09:48,660 --> 00:09:51,360
Dad, what's wrong? Are you hurt?

174
00:09:51,430 --> 00:09:53,830
It's nothing.
I just tweaked it a bit.

175
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,800
What? How did that happen?

176
00:10:01,770 --> 00:10:04,540
What? A robber?

177
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:08,010
Hey, don't worry. I'm fine.
It's nothing serious.

178
00:10:08,150 --> 00:10:10,250
What do you mean
it's nothing serious?

179
00:10:10,350 --> 00:10:13,480
Wait, so you're saying
you caught the robber?

180
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:16,950
What makes you think
you could catch a robber?

181
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:21,130
Well, in the heat of the moment,
I just saw red and jumped in, but...

182
00:10:21,430 --> 00:10:25,330
- I nearly got Dong Ik killed.
- What?

183
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:26,960
What are you talking about?

184
00:10:27,260 --> 00:10:29,300
The robber had a knife
and lunged at Dad,

185
00:10:29,430 --> 00:10:31,040
but Dr. Yang got hurt
protecting him.

186
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:35,210
- What? Bucket?
- Yes.

187
00:10:36,210 --> 00:10:40,040
Wait, so you're saying
Dong Ik was stabbed?

188
00:10:40,380 --> 00:10:45,150
Luckily, it just grazed his side.
The wound isn't deep.

189
00:10:46,350 --> 00:10:49,920
But he's such a scaredy-cat.
He panics if he even sees a bug.

190
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:51,520
I know.

191
00:10:52,790 --> 00:10:55,630
My gosh. Thank goodness.

192
00:10:56,290 --> 00:10:57,930
Wow, I'm so grateful to him.

193
00:10:58,360 --> 00:11:01,230
Tell me about it. He's my lifesaver.

194
00:11:11,110 --> 00:11:14,450
Wow. I feel like a princess.

195
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:18,220
It looks great on you.
Wow, you're so pretty.

196
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:22,650
But Eun Bin,
why are there two pillows?

197
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:26,290
How could I sleep in this bed alone?
Let's sleep here together.

198
00:11:26,790 --> 00:11:29,960
No, it's okay. You sleep in the bed.
I prefer sleeping alone.

199
00:11:30,430 --> 00:11:32,930
Don't you dare ruin my fun.

200
00:11:33,030 --> 00:11:34,570
Being here with you like this...

201
00:11:34,570 --> 00:11:36,170
I feel like we're sisters.
I'm too excited to sleep.

202
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,770
You know you're really cute, right?

203
00:11:40,870 --> 00:11:43,010
- You think I'm cute?
- Yes.

204
00:11:43,510 --> 00:11:46,040
I think Woo Jae finds you
super cute too.

205
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:48,750
Really? Woo Jae said I'm cute?

206
00:11:49,350 --> 00:11:51,020
He didn't say it out loud,

207
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:53,920
but that's totally the look
on his face when he sees you.

208
00:11:54,820 --> 00:11:58,560
I knew it! Whatever.

209
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:01,590
You are really cute.

210
00:12:01,890 --> 00:12:02,960
Thank you.

211
00:12:03,830 --> 00:12:06,100
By the way, how do you know my mom?

212
00:12:06,230 --> 00:12:10,500
Earlier, you were calling her rude
and a weird lady, weren't you?

213
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:12,500
Well...

214
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:16,070
Your mother almost hit me
with her car.

215
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:17,980
- Really?
- Yes.

216
00:12:18,310 --> 00:12:22,450
But instead of apologizing,
she acted like I was the crazy one.

217
00:12:22,510 --> 00:12:25,880
I see. My mom can be like that
sometimes.

218
00:12:26,420 --> 00:12:29,390
She didn't seem too happy
about me sleeping over.

219
00:12:29,450 --> 00:12:33,420
No, don't worry about it.
My mom doesn't hold grudges.

220
00:12:34,430 --> 00:12:35,490
That's a relief.

221
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:39,600
You're not much like
your mom, though.

222
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:41,200
Right?

223
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:43,570
My mom looks so young and pretty,
doesn't she?

224
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:47,640
Actually, she's my stepmom.

225
00:12:48,370 --> 00:12:50,570
- I see.
- Surprised?

226
00:12:50,980 --> 00:12:53,580
Hardly. I was adopted.

227
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,150
Oh, I see.

228
00:12:55,410 --> 00:12:56,410
Surprised?

229
00:12:56,810 --> 00:13:00,450
Hardly.
But you turned out really great.

230
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:03,220
That's because I had
great adoptive parents.

231
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:04,820
Looks like you did, too.

232
00:13:05,390 --> 00:13:09,360
Right?
My stepmom gave me so much love.

233
00:13:10,590 --> 00:13:13,900
We have so much in common, don't we?

234
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:18,240
- Want to stay up all night talking?
- Yes, let's.

235
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:19,700
Yes! Great!

236
00:13:21,010 --> 00:13:23,340
So? What brings you to Korea?

237
00:13:29,780 --> 00:13:34,220
You were tossing and turning.
Why are you up already?

238
00:13:34,450 --> 00:13:36,250
You should skip
your morning exercise today.

239
00:13:36,650 --> 00:13:38,860
No. I need to get out there.

240
00:13:39,290 --> 00:13:40,720
How's your wound? Let me see.

241
00:13:40,790 --> 00:13:43,790
No, I kept an eye on it all night.
It's not oozing. It's fine.

242
00:13:44,730 --> 00:13:46,660
I need to wash my hair.

243
00:13:46,730 --> 00:13:49,670
I'll do it. Just wait a second
while I get your clothes.

244
00:13:49,730 --> 00:13:50,830
No, Se Ri.

245
00:13:51,770 --> 00:13:54,070
I'll take care of it myself
from now on.

246
00:13:55,570 --> 00:13:58,710
Come on.
It's not like it's a big deal.

247
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:01,250
See? It's not even that hard,

248
00:14:01,780 --> 00:14:03,050
but I've always made you do it.

249
00:14:03,580 --> 00:14:07,080
- Don't do it anymore.
- Then what am I supposed to do?

250
00:14:09,020 --> 00:14:10,720
Live your own life.

251
00:14:11,420 --> 00:14:14,160
Do whatever you want,
go wherever you want,

252
00:14:14,490 --> 00:14:16,460
and eat whatever you want.
All right?

253
00:14:17,060 --> 00:14:19,130
I should've told you this
a long time ago.

254
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:22,070
I always said you should,

255
00:14:22,770 --> 00:14:23,830
but I could never keep my promise.

256
00:14:25,970 --> 00:14:26,970
I...

257
00:14:27,710 --> 00:14:30,310
I'm going to get through this
on my own, honey.

258
00:14:31,210 --> 00:14:34,310
This time, I'll prove to you
I've really changed.

259
00:14:40,780 --> 00:14:41,790
All right.

260
00:14:42,090 --> 00:14:44,290
My goodness. What is all this?

261
00:14:44,860 --> 00:14:47,520
Min Seo made it all. American style.

262
00:14:48,330 --> 00:14:50,190
Thank you
for letting me stay the night.

263
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:52,660
You didn't have to do all this.

264
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:57,670
We've got pancakes,
a veggie omelet, tomato soup...

265
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:59,040
And what did you call these again?

266
00:14:59,340 --> 00:15:00,940
Home fries.

267
00:15:01,270 --> 00:15:03,770
You parboil the potatoes
and then pan-fry them in butter.

268
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:07,610
She made all this with stuff
from the fridge. Isn't she amazing?

269
00:15:08,510 --> 00:15:10,810
Yes. It's amazing
she can do all this.

270
00:15:11,780 --> 00:15:15,450
My parents both work, so I learned
by taking care of my siblings.

271
00:15:15,950 --> 00:15:20,660
Mom, she's a med student
at Johns Hopkins.

272
00:15:20,790 --> 00:15:22,490
She's taking a break from school
to travel right now.

273
00:15:23,090 --> 00:15:25,730
Min Seo also helped Ji Hu
with his English homework earlier.

274
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,830
My gosh. Really?

275
00:15:28,570 --> 00:15:31,040
But why do you sleep
at the restaurant?

276
00:15:31,140 --> 00:15:32,400
Oh, the thing is,

277
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,940
I had my travel money stolen
at a guesthouse.

278
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:40,910
My boss will give me an advance,
so I'll find a place to stay soon.

279
00:15:41,710 --> 00:15:45,320
Why don't you stay a few more days
until you find a place? Right, Mom?

280
00:15:46,550 --> 00:15:48,120
You can if you'd like.

281
00:15:48,390 --> 00:15:51,390
No, it's okay.
I was taught not to impose.

282
00:15:51,460 --> 00:15:52,690
One night is more than enough.

283
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:56,330
I wish she'd just stay.
This looks delicious.

284
00:15:57,260 --> 00:15:59,760
- This is it, right?
- Yes, that's good.

285
00:15:59,930 --> 00:16:00,930
- There.
- Thanks.

286
00:16:01,970 --> 00:16:02,970
Are you okay?

287
00:16:03,970 --> 00:16:06,740
Dong Ik is the one who got stabbed.
This is nothing compared to that.

288
00:16:06,970 --> 00:16:08,410
Wait, you're heading out already?

289
00:16:08,970 --> 00:16:10,670
I'm going to go check on Dong Ik.

290
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:14,450
Should I call him and thank him?

291
00:16:15,050 --> 00:16:17,650
Are you that grateful?
Because Dong Ik saved my life?

292
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:19,950
How can you even say that?

293
00:16:21,250 --> 00:16:24,490
I honestly didn't know
he'd go that far for me.

294
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:26,320
I was surprised too.

295
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:29,360
It wasn't a conscious decision,
you know.

296
00:16:29,590 --> 00:16:32,160
It was a protective instinct.
His body just reacted.

297
00:16:32,460 --> 00:16:37,230
Wow. So you're saying deep down
he really cares about me?

298
00:16:38,340 --> 00:16:39,940
You could say that.

299
00:16:48,180 --> 00:16:52,780
- Cooking up a storm so early?
- It's oxtail soup.

300
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:56,190
I simmered it all night
for Dr. Yang.

301
00:16:56,890 --> 00:16:58,060
We had oxtail?

302
00:16:58,160 --> 00:17:02,660
Yes. Your uncle seemed so down,
so I bought some to make it for him.

303
00:17:04,130 --> 00:17:06,630
Is Dad doing any better?

304
00:17:06,730 --> 00:17:11,500
When I saw him this morning,
luckily, it hadn't gotten any worse.

305
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:14,940
Here, it's ready.
Have a bowl before you go, okay?

306
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:19,510
- It's okay. I'm heading out.
- Why? Have some and go with Mom.

307
00:17:20,180 --> 00:17:23,050
I just feel like
going by myself today.

308
00:17:24,650 --> 00:17:27,890
I wonder what's up.
Did you fight with your boyfriend?

309
00:17:28,090 --> 00:17:31,020
I'm not telling you.
I'm heading out.

310
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:50,870
Morning, Princess.
Did you sleep well?

311
00:17:51,310 --> 00:17:53,840
I just got up.
I'm about to get ready for work.

312
00:17:56,350 --> 00:17:57,350
Can you give me...

313
00:17:59,150 --> 00:18:03,320
some time to think about it?

314
00:18:09,290 --> 00:18:10,430
How's the wound?

315
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:13,960
It's fine,
aside from a little throbbing.

316
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:17,330
Gosh, Dad. Why did you have to
jump in like that?

317
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:19,740
It's a miracle it wasn't any worse.

318
00:18:23,210 --> 00:18:25,580
Father, what are you staring at?

319
00:18:26,040 --> 00:18:29,350
It's just...
That part-timer looks familiar.

320
00:18:30,510 --> 00:18:31,520
Me?

321
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:33,450
Dad, there you go again.

322
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:36,390
That's funny. I thought so, too.

323
00:18:36,590 --> 00:18:40,490
The first time I met Min Seo, I felt
I'd seen her somewhere before.

324
00:18:40,560 --> 00:18:43,390
- Doesn't everyone think so?
- Really? I don't see it.

325
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:47,360
I guess I just have
one of those faces.

326
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:51,140
Wait, you made all of this yourself?

327
00:18:51,740 --> 00:18:52,740
Yes.

328
00:18:54,640 --> 00:18:58,010
Why won't this thing work?

329
00:18:58,280 --> 00:19:00,040
For crying out loud. Use this.

330
00:19:00,410 --> 00:19:01,450
Goodness!

331
00:19:01,810 --> 00:19:03,750
What? You're so jumpy.

332
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:06,950
Hey, why is my heart
pounding so hard?

333
00:19:07,820 --> 00:19:10,120
Honey, I think it's starting.

334
00:19:10,190 --> 00:19:13,260
From getting stabbed last night.
What's it called? That thing.

335
00:19:13,590 --> 00:19:16,090
Right. What was that called again?

336
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:18,330
It sounds like
post-traumatic stress disorder.

337
00:19:21,170 --> 00:19:24,330
Oh, I mean, PTSD.

338
00:19:24,940 --> 00:19:27,440
Right. Post-traumatic...

339
00:19:28,270 --> 00:19:31,640
Wait, so you're saying
when my brain sees a knife,

340
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:33,310
it thinks I'm in danger?

341
00:19:33,610 --> 00:19:34,780
Yes, exactly.

342
00:19:35,150 --> 00:19:39,150
Limit your trigger exposure for now.
Especially sharp things.

343
00:19:39,420 --> 00:19:41,650
You're such a coward.
Why did you jump in like that?

344
00:19:42,190 --> 00:19:44,090
It really is a relief you're okay.

345
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:46,190
Se Ri, you're going to
have your hands full.

346
00:19:46,490 --> 00:19:48,290
He's going to be
such a baby about it.

347
00:19:48,730 --> 00:19:49,730
No!

348
00:19:50,190 --> 00:19:51,530
I promise I won't be like that
anymore.

349
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:56,400
From now on, don't rely on Se Ri.
Take care of yourselves, you hear?

350
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:59,700
- We're worried about you, Uncle.
- Exactly!

351
00:19:59,770 --> 00:20:00,770
Bingo.

352
00:20:01,170 --> 00:20:02,170
Why, you little...

353
00:20:03,510 --> 00:20:07,540
Dad, Se Ri decided to start studying
and look for a place for her shop.

354
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:11,520
It's about time.
That's music to my ears.

355
00:20:20,860 --> 00:20:21,960
My gosh.

356
00:20:22,290 --> 00:20:23,560
Good morning, sir.
Did you sleep well?

357
00:20:24,030 --> 00:20:25,030
Yes.

358
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:27,700
Hey! What brings you here
so early in the morning?

359
00:20:28,230 --> 00:20:30,700
What do you think?
I was worried about you.

360
00:20:31,170 --> 00:20:34,140
You must have been so shocked
when Dong Ik got hurt.

361
00:20:34,910 --> 00:20:36,770
He wasn't seriously injured,
so that's all that matters.

362
00:20:37,740 --> 00:20:38,740
Yes, sir.

363
00:20:40,110 --> 00:20:42,880
Hey, did you run a fever
or get the chills last night?

364
00:20:42,980 --> 00:20:45,880
No. I think this much pain
is to be expected,

365
00:20:46,020 --> 00:20:47,750
and I don't have
any other signs of infection.

366
00:20:48,790 --> 00:20:49,820
Good. That's a relief.

367
00:20:50,220 --> 00:20:53,660
I'll take you to and from work
until you're all better.

368
00:20:53,790 --> 00:20:55,260
Come on, let's get going.

369
00:20:58,630 --> 00:20:59,900
Hey, Jeong Han.

370
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:03,030
Did your daughter say anything
to you yesterday?

371
00:21:03,370 --> 00:21:04,900
What? No.

372
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:08,310
- Why? Did something happen?
- It's nothing. Never mind.

373
00:21:11,140 --> 00:21:12,140
Right.

374
00:21:12,740 --> 00:21:14,310
I'll just put it off for a day.
Just one day.

375
00:21:15,110 --> 00:21:17,680
Just one more day.
Savor this happiness, Yang Dong Ik.

376
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:22,720
- Hey, easy. Mind your step.
- Okay.

377
00:21:27,420 --> 00:21:28,660
(Taehan Group)

378
00:21:48,550 --> 00:21:50,280
You look like you didn't sleep well.

379
00:21:53,550 --> 00:21:56,550
You don't look like
you slept well either, Director.

380
00:21:57,790 --> 00:22:00,660
I felt too guilty and ashamed.

381
00:22:01,690 --> 00:22:03,790
You have nothing to be sorry for,
Director.

382
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:07,630
Have a good day.

383
00:22:09,930 --> 00:22:11,000
Wait.

384
00:22:11,840 --> 00:22:12,840
Yes?

385
00:22:13,570 --> 00:22:14,970
Dr. Yang...

386
00:22:15,610 --> 00:22:17,010
He got hurt yesterday.

387
00:22:21,180 --> 00:22:23,980
Hey. Well, it's not that serious.

388
00:22:24,680 --> 00:22:25,850
I just got a small cut from a knife.

389
00:22:26,380 --> 00:22:27,880
You're okay, though, right?

390
00:22:28,390 --> 00:22:29,390
I'm fine.

391
00:22:30,050 --> 00:22:31,350
Did you call because
you were worried about me?

392
00:22:31,620 --> 00:22:34,060
Why haven't you told Dr. Gong?

393
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:36,660
I told you to confess that
you staged the whole thing.

394
00:22:36,990 --> 00:22:38,830
I was going to tell him when we met.

395
00:22:39,460 --> 00:22:41,060
But the timing wasn't right,
you know?

396
00:22:41,730 --> 00:22:44,300
Listen, your father almost died.
Is that what matters to you now?

397
00:22:44,970 --> 00:22:46,100
Yes, it's important to me.

398
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:48,670
Fine! I'll tell him. I said I would.

399
00:22:49,410 --> 00:22:52,310
And do it yourself.
Don't make my stepmother do it.

400
00:22:52,580 --> 00:22:55,680
I said I got it!
I'll do it, okay? I'll do it.

401
00:22:58,380 --> 00:22:59,750
I swear, that kid...

402
00:23:00,250 --> 00:23:01,990
Who did he get that from?
So darn rigid.

403
00:23:05,360 --> 00:23:06,960
(3H Acupressure Bed)

404
00:23:07,020 --> 00:23:09,160
- How does that feel?
- It's amazing.

405
00:23:12,830 --> 00:23:16,230
You're back. Care for another look
at the model I showed you last time?

406
00:23:16,370 --> 00:23:20,640
No. I actually came to ask
about something today.

407
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:23,240
- Sure, what is it?
- It's about...

408
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:26,940
that ad you have posted.
The one for new franchise owners.

409
00:23:37,790 --> 00:23:39,920
Hey. What are you doing here?

410
00:23:40,260 --> 00:23:41,890
I'm organizing the files
for the meeting.

411
00:23:43,090 --> 00:23:44,930
No, I mean,
why are you doing it here?

412
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:49,230
I was on the Design Team, remember?
This is my desk.

413
00:23:56,710 --> 00:23:59,880
Here's the photo shoot concept
and the final list of outfits.

414
00:24:01,410 --> 00:24:02,950
We've finished Dr. Han's fitting...

415
00:24:02,950 --> 00:24:05,680
and chosen Black Edition
for the main cut.

416
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:10,920
I like it. It really captures
that high-end, modern feel.

417
00:24:11,590 --> 00:24:14,720
Who's in charge of on-set direction
for the photo shoot?

418
00:24:16,090 --> 00:24:17,690
I'll be handling that.

419
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:20,660
I see.

420
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:24,330
Looks like those two had a fight,
doesn't it?

421
00:24:25,270 --> 00:24:27,470
I wouldn't know anything about that,
Vice President.

422
00:24:28,470 --> 00:24:33,240
PR wants a behind-the-scenes video
at the shoot.

423
00:24:33,340 --> 00:24:36,010
- What does the Design Team think?
- I think that's a great idea.

424
00:24:36,450 --> 00:24:40,320
Showing a natural side of Dr. Han
could increase brand relatability.

425
00:24:41,050 --> 00:24:42,490
Ms. Gong, what are your thoughts?

426
00:24:47,220 --> 00:24:49,130
Yes, I think it's a good idea
as well.

427
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:54,200
After the shoot, we'll also conduct
a video interview with Dr. Han.

428
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:56,270
Okay, in that case,

429
00:24:56,600 --> 00:25:00,300
I'll prepare the interview questions
and talking points.

430
00:25:01,770 --> 00:25:02,770
Good.

431
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:07,380
Find out what's going on with them.
Now.

432
00:25:07,980 --> 00:25:09,750
We should probably stay out of it.

433
00:25:11,350 --> 00:25:12,380
Understood.

434
00:25:29,330 --> 00:25:32,800
Gosh, it's so obvious
they had a fight.

435
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:36,470
- Who? Who fought?
- You did.

436
00:25:37,940 --> 00:25:38,940
With Director Yang.

437
00:25:40,210 --> 00:25:42,350
How can an employee pick a fight
with a director?

438
00:25:43,350 --> 00:25:46,280
So, you hit him then?
He looked like he'd been hit.

439
00:25:46,650 --> 00:25:48,250
I should probably hit you first.

440
00:25:48,790 --> 00:25:50,820
Seriously, mind your own business.
Please.

441
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:54,930
But I thought your families made up.
Why are you two on bad terms again?

442
00:26:00,260 --> 00:26:02,300
Come on. You're so mean.

443
00:26:02,970 --> 00:26:05,440
Hey, Gong Ju Ah.
This whole cold shoulder thing...

444
00:26:05,500 --> 00:26:06,500
Are we doing that or not?

445
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:07,840
We're doing that.

446
00:26:09,010 --> 00:26:13,480
Come on, I swear I'll never tell
the VP anything again.

447
00:26:13,540 --> 00:26:15,780
You want me to sign it in blood?
Hey, look.

448
00:26:17,050 --> 00:26:18,380
- Do it.
- You're serious?

449
00:26:18,450 --> 00:26:19,450
Do it!

450
00:26:42,740 --> 00:26:46,280
Are you working at the Design Office
just to avoid me?

451
00:26:47,280 --> 00:26:48,280
Yes.

452
00:26:48,980 --> 00:26:52,250
Because I'm afraid I'll cave
if I see you.

453
00:26:54,050 --> 00:26:57,090
But if you won't even see me,
what am I supposed to do?

454
00:26:57,490 --> 00:27:01,990
I said we needed time to think,
not that we couldn't see each other.

455
00:27:04,390 --> 00:27:07,660
Yesterday...
Why didn't you tell your family?

456
00:27:08,260 --> 00:27:11,700
They'd be devastated
if they found out.

457
00:27:12,470 --> 00:27:16,670
Besides, after yesterday,
my dad now sees Dr. Yang...

458
00:27:16,740 --> 00:27:19,010
as his lifesaver.

459
00:27:19,740 --> 00:27:21,510
My father will tell them.

460
00:27:21,780 --> 00:27:24,510
He meant to mention it
yesterday but couldn't.

461
00:27:26,550 --> 00:27:30,220
Could you just ask him
not to say anything?

462
00:27:31,760 --> 00:27:33,360
So you want to just sweep this
under the rug?

463
00:27:34,190 --> 00:27:37,060
I'd rather our parents
just didn't know.

464
00:27:37,830 --> 00:27:40,930
Let's just figure out
where we stand.

465
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:46,040
How much time do you need to think?

466
00:27:48,540 --> 00:27:49,970
I don't know.

467
00:27:50,810 --> 00:27:53,410
I'm just not
in the right headspace yet.

468
00:27:55,750 --> 00:27:56,750
I understand.

469
00:27:57,480 --> 00:28:00,420
I'll accept whatever you decide.

470
00:28:00,620 --> 00:28:05,190
So don't feel pressured.
Take all the time you need.

471
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:07,020
I can wait as long as you need.

472
00:28:08,930 --> 00:28:10,090
In that case...

473
00:28:10,160 --> 00:28:14,330
Can I stay in the Design Office
until I've figured things out?

474
00:28:26,940 --> 00:28:30,550
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

475
00:28:30,550 --> 00:28:31,650
What brings you here?

476
00:28:33,350 --> 00:28:34,950
My mom wants you and your father...

477
00:28:35,350 --> 00:28:38,460
to come to our clinic to eat.
She made oxtail soup.

478
00:28:39,460 --> 00:28:40,820
Okay.

479
00:28:42,030 --> 00:28:43,030
Listen.

480
00:28:44,490 --> 00:28:46,700
Thank you for saving my brother.

481
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:48,200
What?

482
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:51,270
I wonder if I could've done the same
in your shoes,

483
00:28:52,370 --> 00:28:54,470
but I don't think I could have.

484
00:28:55,440 --> 00:28:57,370
Thank you so much.
For saving my brother's life.

485
00:28:58,270 --> 00:29:01,680
If anything happened to my brother,
I couldn't have gone on.

486
00:29:01,740 --> 00:29:02,750
So...

487
00:29:03,580 --> 00:29:05,980
you didn't just save my brother.
It's like you saved me, too.

488
00:29:06,020 --> 00:29:07,020
Dong Ik.

489
00:29:08,150 --> 00:29:09,290
Thank you. Truly.

490
00:29:10,320 --> 00:29:11,550
You two are really something.

491
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:13,790
You're both so dramatic.

492
00:29:14,590 --> 00:29:16,790
From now on, don't leave me out.
Let me join in.

493
00:29:17,690 --> 00:29:18,700
All right.

494
00:29:19,500 --> 00:29:20,500
Let's all hang out together.

495
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:25,300
Let me know
if you need more green onions.

496
00:29:27,100 --> 00:29:29,370
By the way, where's Nurse Oh?

497
00:29:29,740 --> 00:29:32,580
She went to take some
to the police substation.

498
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:35,610
They're our lifesavers too,
aren't they?

499
00:29:36,010 --> 00:29:37,010
That's true.

500
00:29:37,310 --> 00:29:41,050
After we eat, I'll hose the front.
Want to join me?

501
00:29:41,120 --> 00:29:42,890
Yes, sounds good.

502
00:29:44,090 --> 00:29:45,690
Dae Han, you'll help out too, right?

503
00:29:46,160 --> 00:29:48,930
Me? Yes, of course.

504
00:29:49,590 --> 00:29:50,660
Are you done pouting now?

505
00:29:51,160 --> 00:29:52,760
Who said I was pouting?

506
00:29:52,930 --> 00:29:55,430
Please add more salt
if it's too bland.

507
00:29:55,500 --> 00:29:56,930
Right. Here you go.

508
00:29:59,800 --> 00:30:01,570
My, it's seasoned perfectly.

509
00:30:02,210 --> 00:30:03,810
And the broth is so rich.

510
00:30:06,080 --> 00:30:08,010
You made this for me?

511
00:30:09,080 --> 00:30:12,480
I'm sorry this is all I could do.

512
00:30:13,480 --> 00:30:16,520
So eat up. I made plenty.

513
00:30:18,590 --> 00:30:19,960
By the way, sir.

514
00:30:20,990 --> 00:30:23,830
I have a patient
who keeps getting indigestion,

515
00:30:23,930 --> 00:30:26,760
and they feel bloated
even if they eat just a little.

516
00:30:27,460 --> 00:30:29,930
We've done
an ultrasound and endoscopy,

517
00:30:29,930 --> 00:30:31,500
and they've been to a big hospital,

518
00:30:31,570 --> 00:30:33,400
but we haven't found
anything abnormal.

519
00:30:34,340 --> 00:30:37,710
So, how would you approach this
with traditional medicine?

520
00:30:37,910 --> 00:30:41,140
Well, I'd have to check their pulse
to be sure, but...

521
00:30:41,640 --> 00:30:43,710
if the circulation of qi and blood
isn't smooth,

522
00:30:44,010 --> 00:30:46,750
it can cause a solar plexus blockage
and lead to indigestion.

523
00:30:47,080 --> 00:30:48,950
I see. Then...

524
00:30:49,390 --> 00:30:51,520
would you be willing
to check their pulse?

525
00:30:52,260 --> 00:30:54,160
If we only manage this
with medication,

526
00:30:54,220 --> 00:30:57,160
long-term use could cause
some negative side effects.

527
00:30:58,230 --> 00:31:03,070
So, if you're willing, sir,
maybe we could combine treatments.

528
00:31:04,230 --> 00:31:05,470
Dr. Gong, are you...

529
00:31:06,300 --> 00:31:07,840
proposing a joint consultation?

530
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:10,410
Yes. As I recall,

531
00:31:11,110 --> 00:31:14,040
you and my father used to do it
from time to time.

532
00:31:15,750 --> 00:31:19,050
- Right, they did.
- Yes.

533
00:31:19,750 --> 00:31:20,780
Dad.

534
00:31:24,490 --> 00:31:26,760
Gosh, thank you, sir.

535
00:31:28,020 --> 00:31:29,030
Thanks, Jeong Han.

536
00:31:29,330 --> 00:31:32,560
Oh, please.
I should've done this sooner.

537
00:31:32,660 --> 00:31:35,000
Hey, let's at least get along
from now on, okay?

538
00:31:36,530 --> 00:31:37,870
This is nice, in more ways than one.

539
00:31:38,530 --> 00:31:41,540
How about a toast
with our bone broth?

540
00:31:41,770 --> 00:31:45,540
If we toast with the bone broth...
You can't chug it since it's hot!

541
00:31:46,280 --> 00:31:47,280
It's hot.

542
00:31:48,140 --> 00:31:49,580
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

543
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:53,920
Wow, this is delicious.

544
00:31:54,480 --> 00:31:55,920
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

545
00:31:56,290 --> 00:31:58,020
- Spray here, too!
- Oh, here.

546
00:31:58,090 --> 00:31:59,360
Hey, this is great.

547
00:32:00,420 --> 00:32:02,430
- Hey, let me wipe it.
- You want to?

548
00:32:02,490 --> 00:32:03,490
- Yes, go ahead.
- All right.

549
00:32:03,560 --> 00:32:04,660
- Let's wipe as we go.
- All clean.

550
00:32:04,660 --> 00:32:06,600
- Right?
- Hey, wipe over here, too.

551
00:32:06,600 --> 00:32:09,330
- Sure. Here.
- Hey! You've got to wipe here, too!

552
00:32:11,330 --> 00:32:13,900
Hey, is it raining or what?
Here, let me have that.

553
00:32:13,900 --> 00:32:16,010
- Why?
- Hold on. Attack!

554
00:32:18,110 --> 00:32:21,140
- What are you guys doing?
- Get this spot. This spot here.

555
00:32:21,140 --> 00:32:22,250
Hey, you can't even spray right?

556
00:32:23,510 --> 00:32:26,720
- Your turn!
- Hey, give it here! Stop it!

557
00:32:27,050 --> 00:32:29,290
- Stop! Stop it!
- Why? What's wrong?

558
00:32:29,350 --> 00:32:30,550
- Clean it up, quick!
- All right.

559
00:32:30,550 --> 00:32:33,160
Mom told us to clean.
Are you cleaning or what?

560
00:32:33,760 --> 00:32:34,920
Jeong Han, no!

561
00:32:35,560 --> 00:32:36,690
Hey!

562
00:32:53,880 --> 00:32:55,680
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

563
00:33:06,390 --> 00:33:07,390
Oh, well...

564
00:33:07,690 --> 00:33:12,630
Gosh, if you're worried, just go.
Stop being so antsy.

565
00:33:12,630 --> 00:33:14,730
- Oh, no, sir, I'm fine.
- Goodness, here.

566
00:33:14,800 --> 00:33:16,670
(Warm and Reliable Police,
Onjeong Police Substation)

567
00:33:17,000 --> 00:33:19,500
- Hello!
- Perfect timing.

568
00:33:19,740 --> 00:33:21,470
Oh, you're here. Hello.

569
00:33:22,110 --> 00:33:24,110
Here's some bone broth.

570
00:33:24,210 --> 00:33:25,980
The pharmacist asked me
to drop it off.

571
00:33:26,110 --> 00:33:29,180
- My goodness. Thank you.
- Oh, my.

572
00:33:30,010 --> 00:33:31,010
What?

573
00:33:31,810 --> 00:33:32,820
Oh, no.

574
00:33:35,450 --> 00:33:40,020
Now that we've caught the suspect,
I'll go reassure the shopkeepers.

575
00:33:41,020 --> 00:33:45,260
- Gosh, I knew it. Seriously.
- No, it's just...

576
00:33:46,630 --> 00:33:47,630
Stay still.

577
00:33:48,730 --> 00:33:49,800
Don't be such a baby.

578
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:55,300
Thank you so much for yesterday.

579
00:33:56,210 --> 00:33:59,340
It was nothing.
I should have gotten there sooner.

580
00:34:01,940 --> 00:34:03,310
You were really scared, weren't you?

581
00:34:04,610 --> 00:34:06,480
Did you sleep okay?

582
00:34:07,420 --> 00:34:09,520
I didn't sleep well at all.

583
00:34:11,990 --> 00:34:13,220
So you were really scared.

584
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:16,390
No. I was too excited.

585
00:34:17,430 --> 00:34:18,430
What?

586
00:34:19,300 --> 00:34:23,530
You were incredibly cool yesterday.
I've totally fallen for you.

587
00:34:23,970 --> 00:34:24,970
Oh, well...

588
00:34:25,670 --> 00:34:26,670
Okay.

589
00:34:27,100 --> 00:34:28,870
There, all done.

590
00:34:46,020 --> 00:34:47,160
All right, put it down.

591
00:34:48,220 --> 00:34:49,230
Oh, okay.

592
00:34:52,660 --> 00:34:55,900
Yes, hello? Yes.
Yes, this is Gong Dae Han.

593
00:34:56,470 --> 00:34:58,800
There was an early withdrawal
from your installment account,

594
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:02,670
so you lost your preferential rate
and long-term benefits.

595
00:35:02,940 --> 00:35:04,410
Right.

596
00:35:04,910 --> 00:35:06,710
Just go ahead and close the account.

597
00:35:08,140 --> 00:35:10,610
Okay, I'll head over to the bank.
Yes.

598
00:35:10,780 --> 00:35:13,020
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

599
00:35:19,790 --> 00:35:22,290
Yes, Dad.
I confirmed the money came through.

600
00:35:23,430 --> 00:35:26,700
Okay, I'll ensure it goes smoothly.
Thanks.

601
00:35:32,700 --> 00:35:33,700
Oh, boy.

602
00:35:35,270 --> 00:35:38,270
Come on,
I told you I'd peel that for you.

603
00:35:38,340 --> 00:35:40,440
I can do it myself, you know.

604
00:35:40,680 --> 00:35:42,810
Of course, you can.
That's not what I'm saying.

605
00:35:43,380 --> 00:35:47,480
So let me do it. Besides, Dad said
not to make you do everything.

606
00:35:47,950 --> 00:35:51,220
Honestly, seeing Min Seo was
a real wake-up call for me.

607
00:35:51,520 --> 00:35:53,290
She's younger than me,
but she's so good at everything.

608
00:35:55,630 --> 00:35:59,960
Wow, Se Ri,
our Eun Bin is finally growing up.

609
00:36:01,160 --> 00:36:02,230
Tell me about it.

610
00:36:02,830 --> 00:36:04,930
So, Se Ri,
how was the mattress store?

611
00:36:05,200 --> 00:36:08,000
It looked promising,
so I'm going to HQ for a meeting.

612
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:10,440
What about you, Dong Suk?
When do you sign the store lease?

613
00:36:10,540 --> 00:36:13,180
Right now, actually.
My father just sent the deposit.

614
00:36:14,740 --> 00:36:18,680
Unbelievable. Grandpa and Dad...
I need money, too.

615
00:36:18,750 --> 00:36:21,080
They're only investing in Mom
and Aunt Dong Suk.

616
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:22,890
Eun Bin.

617
00:36:23,250 --> 00:36:26,020
Why don't you try raising
the start-up money yourself?

618
00:36:26,420 --> 00:36:28,420
And how am I supposed to do that?

619
00:36:28,760 --> 00:36:30,530
Get a part-time job like Min Seo.

620
00:36:30,760 --> 00:36:33,260
I've never had to do
that kind of hard labor.

621
00:36:35,160 --> 00:36:36,430
By the way, Dong Suk.

622
00:36:36,970 --> 00:36:38,900
I feel so bad about
Ji Hu's tutoring.

623
00:36:39,640 --> 00:36:42,710
Why? Did things fall through
with that star tutor from Yeonjong?

624
00:36:43,110 --> 00:36:46,540
Yes. It seems they're overbooked,
so scheduling is difficult.

625
00:36:47,080 --> 00:36:48,510
I'll find someone else.

626
00:36:48,610 --> 00:36:51,880
No, it's okay. I'll take over now.
You don't have to worry anymore.

627
00:36:53,220 --> 00:36:56,990
You've got to be kidding me.
Hello? What about me?

628
00:36:57,620 --> 00:37:00,220
What? You're going to tutor Ji Hu?

629
00:37:00,290 --> 00:37:03,690
Hey! Are you trying to ruin my son?
You barely graduated yourself.

630
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:05,660
Barely is still a pass, not a fail.

631
00:37:05,660 --> 00:37:08,030
You think
I can't teach a middle schooler?

632
00:37:09,270 --> 00:37:10,700
Then, Dong Suk,

633
00:37:11,330 --> 00:37:16,040
why don't we let Eun Bin try it,
just until we find a proper tutor?

634
00:37:16,540 --> 00:37:18,070
Come on, Se Ri.

635
00:37:18,170 --> 00:37:21,040
It'll be easier to convince Father
if she works.

636
00:37:21,810 --> 00:37:22,980
Just for a little while, okay?

637
00:37:23,250 --> 00:37:25,350
Even if I agree,
I bet Ji Hu will say no.

638
00:37:25,410 --> 00:37:28,350
- I'll ask him.
- There's no point in asking.

639
00:37:29,150 --> 00:37:30,150
We'll see when I ask him.

640
00:37:30,690 --> 00:37:32,290
The phone is turned off.
Please leave a message...

641
00:37:32,390 --> 00:37:35,730
What? Why is his phone off?

642
00:37:36,190 --> 00:37:37,190
It's off?

643
00:37:38,330 --> 00:37:39,830
He should be at his academy by now.

644
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:41,730
Maybe his class has already started.

645
00:37:46,540 --> 00:37:48,000
Who could this be?

646
00:37:49,470 --> 00:37:51,640
- Yes.
- Hello?

647
00:37:52,010 --> 00:37:53,010
Yes, who is this?

648
00:37:53,340 --> 00:37:56,250
- Is this Yang Dong Suk?
- Yes, this is she.

649
00:37:57,280 --> 00:37:58,650
You're Min Ji Hu's mother, right?

650
00:38:00,650 --> 00:38:03,590
- Who is this?
- I'm putting him on. Talk to him.

651
00:38:04,090 --> 00:38:07,790
Hello? What are you talking about?
Hello? Ji Hu?

652
00:38:08,390 --> 00:38:09,390
Mom.

653
00:38:11,660 --> 00:38:14,230
Ji Hu! Hello?

654
00:38:14,560 --> 00:38:16,700
Where are you? Ji Hu,
where are you right now?

655
00:38:17,630 --> 00:38:18,630
Hello?

656
00:38:18,630 --> 00:38:21,470
Who are you? Why do you have my son?

657
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:24,240
Where are you? Tell me now!

658
00:38:24,710 --> 00:38:25,710
Ms. Yang Dong Suk.

659
00:38:26,140 --> 00:38:28,040
If you want your son to live,
you'll listen to me carefully.

660
00:38:30,780 --> 00:38:32,820
I'm on my way now, just a minute.

661
00:38:33,380 --> 00:38:35,750
Yes, I'm in front of the bank now.

662
00:38:36,590 --> 00:38:38,050
Dong Suk! What's wrong?
What's going on?

663
00:38:38,820 --> 00:38:41,660
I'm about to wire the money,
so don't you touch Ji Hu.

664
00:38:41,920 --> 00:38:44,390
Don't you dare touch a hair
on my son's head.

665
00:38:44,660 --> 00:38:45,660
Hey, Dong Suk!

666
00:38:45,900 --> 00:38:49,200
Let go! I have to go inside!
I need to send the money!

667
00:38:49,270 --> 00:38:51,130
Wait, what's this about Ji Hu?
What's going on?

668
00:38:52,330 --> 00:38:54,700
- Ji Hu's been kidnapped.
- What?

669
00:38:54,700 --> 00:38:57,240
Some guy says he has him.

670
00:38:58,970 --> 00:39:01,910
Hello? I'm going to send
5,000 dollars right now.

671
00:39:02,410 --> 00:39:06,980
I'll send it. As soon as you get it,
you let my son go, all right?

672
00:39:07,120 --> 00:39:10,390
- Give me that.
- What are you doing? Are you crazy?

673
00:39:11,090 --> 00:39:14,620
He told me not to hang up!
Why did you hang up? He said not to!

674
00:39:14,690 --> 00:39:17,460
- What right do you have to hang up?
- Dong Suk!

675
00:39:17,930 --> 00:39:19,400
This is a voice phishing scam!

676
00:39:19,830 --> 00:39:23,830
No, it's not! I talked to Ji Hu.
I heard his voice!

677
00:39:23,930 --> 00:39:26,440
That's so you can't hang up
and call Ji Hu.

678
00:39:26,740 --> 00:39:31,040
His phone's been off all this time.
That man has my son.

679
00:39:31,140 --> 00:39:34,380
He said he'd kill Ji Hu
if I don't send the money!

680
00:39:34,680 --> 00:39:37,410
Dong Suk, look at me.

681
00:39:38,010 --> 00:39:41,020
Who would kill someone for a measly
5,000 dollars? Think about it.

682
00:39:41,950 --> 00:39:45,550
You see this exact scam on the news
all the time. Can't you see that?

683
00:39:45,990 --> 00:39:49,460
Gosh, I don't know. What do I do?

684
00:39:49,530 --> 00:39:52,390
Dong Suk. Go to the police station
right now and file a report.

685
00:39:52,900 --> 00:39:55,230
Where's Ji Hu supposed to be?
Tell me.

686
00:39:55,300 --> 00:39:56,300
I'll go get Ji Hu.

687
00:40:02,370 --> 00:40:04,010
Ji Hu! Min Ji Hu!

688
00:40:07,710 --> 00:40:10,610
- Ji Hu.
- I'm not him.

689
00:40:11,010 --> 00:40:12,050
Sorry.

690
00:40:14,350 --> 00:40:17,450
Excuse me. Do you happen to know
where Ji Hu is?

691
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:18,920
Sorry, I don't.

692
00:40:19,460 --> 00:40:22,490
Where on earth did he go?
Ji Hu! Min Ji Hu!

693
00:40:23,160 --> 00:40:26,160
Oh, who are you?

694
00:40:26,630 --> 00:40:27,630
Me?

695
00:40:28,830 --> 00:40:30,170
Do you happen to know
where Ji Hu is?

696
00:40:30,930 --> 00:40:33,070
Why was your phone off?
Why weren't you picking up?

697
00:40:34,040 --> 00:40:36,070
- What?
- Call your mom. Right now.

698
00:40:36,840 --> 00:40:38,870
Do you know how frantic your mom
has been looking for you?

699
00:40:40,210 --> 00:40:41,310
Call her. Now.

700
00:40:41,510 --> 00:40:43,150
My battery died.

701
00:40:44,150 --> 00:40:45,410
Good grief.

702
00:40:50,650 --> 00:40:51,650
Here, use mine.

703
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:56,360
Is that your dad?

704
00:40:57,060 --> 00:40:58,060
He's not my dad.

705
00:41:03,970 --> 00:41:07,670
(Onjeong Police Substation)

706
00:41:07,970 --> 00:41:10,310
Dae Han? Where are you?
Did you find Ji Hu?

707
00:41:10,740 --> 00:41:12,470
Mom, it's me.

708
00:41:13,440 --> 00:41:14,810
Ji Hu!

709
00:41:15,410 --> 00:41:17,780
Why was your phone off? Why?

710
00:41:18,650 --> 00:41:19,720
I ran out of battery.

711
00:41:20,580 --> 00:41:21,620
Mom, where are you?

712
00:41:22,180 --> 00:41:23,620
Why were you looking for me?
Is something wrong?

713
00:41:25,120 --> 00:41:28,160
From now on, carry a charger.
Got it?

714
00:41:29,160 --> 00:41:31,460
I was just so worried.

715
00:41:33,630 --> 00:41:35,970
All right.
Hurry up and get to the academy.

716
00:41:36,730 --> 00:41:37,730
Okay.

717
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:44,810
- What's going on?
- They said you were kidnapped...

718
00:41:49,310 --> 00:41:51,110
Looks like your mom got a scare
from a voice phishing call.

719
00:41:51,750 --> 00:41:52,750
Again?

720
00:41:53,450 --> 00:41:55,550
Seriously, this has happened
to so many kids at our academy.

721
00:41:55,920 --> 00:41:57,590
Someone must have leaked
all our information.

722
00:41:57,950 --> 00:41:58,950
Right?

723
00:41:59,050 --> 00:42:01,360
You should be at your academy.
What are you doing here?

724
00:42:01,690 --> 00:42:03,160
Your mom even called the academy.

725
00:42:03,790 --> 00:42:04,790
I'm sorry.

726
00:42:05,630 --> 00:42:06,960
It's my 100-day anniversary
with my girlfriend.

727
00:42:08,060 --> 00:42:10,430
- I'm sorry.
- You don't have to apologize to me.

728
00:42:10,730 --> 00:42:11,730
Here, eat up.

729
00:42:12,200 --> 00:42:13,840
Finish this and make sure
you go to your academy.

730
00:42:18,010 --> 00:42:19,040
Wait.

731
00:42:20,480 --> 00:42:22,340
Please don't tell my mom.

732
00:42:24,450 --> 00:42:25,450
Goodness.

733
00:42:32,190 --> 00:42:33,190
Here.

734
00:42:35,620 --> 00:42:36,630
It's your 100-day anniversary,
right?

735
00:42:37,830 --> 00:42:38,890
Go buy your girlfriend some flowers.

736
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:40,830
Girls love flowers.

737
00:42:42,060 --> 00:42:43,070
Bye.

738
00:42:49,570 --> 00:42:50,570
Dong Suk!

739
00:42:52,270 --> 00:42:55,210
Dong Suk! Goodness, hey.

740
00:42:58,810 --> 00:42:59,820
Are you okay?

741
00:43:01,120 --> 00:43:03,120
I was so stupid, wasn't I?

742
00:43:03,990 --> 00:43:05,450
What are you talking about?
Of course not.

743
00:43:07,060 --> 00:43:08,660
I would've done the same thing.
Anyone would have.

744
00:43:09,730 --> 00:43:11,060
I was so scared...

745
00:43:11,790 --> 00:43:13,330
I was out of my mind.

746
00:43:14,930 --> 00:43:17,170
Ji Hu is all I have left.

747
00:43:18,170 --> 00:43:20,700
The thought of something happening
to him, too...

748
00:43:26,640 --> 00:43:29,040
Thank you, Dae Han.
Thank you so much.

749
00:43:37,790 --> 00:43:39,050
Come on, now.

750
00:43:40,620 --> 00:43:41,720
If you're ever in trouble,

751
00:43:42,930 --> 00:43:44,160
you should've called your boyfriend.

752
00:43:45,190 --> 00:43:48,960
Something like this happens,
and he doesn't even show up?

753
00:43:49,600 --> 00:43:51,170
What boyfriend? I don't have one.

754
00:43:53,770 --> 00:43:54,770
What did you say?

755
00:43:55,340 --> 00:43:56,940
As if anyone would be interested
in someone like me.

756
00:43:58,510 --> 00:44:01,480
What are you talking about?
Everyone said you had a boyfriend.

757
00:44:03,610 --> 00:44:04,910
They were talking about you.

758
00:44:07,680 --> 00:44:09,750
- Me?
- Yes.

759
00:44:10,220 --> 00:44:14,090
They must've gotten the wrong idea.
I don't have a boyfriend.

760
00:44:20,930 --> 00:44:21,930
So that's what it was?

761
00:44:22,500 --> 00:44:23,600
Yes, you dummy.

762
00:44:30,410 --> 00:44:31,410
Dong Suk!

763
00:44:36,050 --> 00:44:37,410
Who would be interested
in someone like you?

764
00:44:42,180 --> 00:44:43,190
Me. I like you.

765
00:44:44,690 --> 00:44:45,950
I'm the one who worries about you.

766
00:44:46,920 --> 00:44:48,120
I'm the one who misses you.

767
00:44:51,730 --> 00:44:53,000
I like you. A lot.

768
00:45:19,690 --> 00:45:22,020
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

769
00:45:24,360 --> 00:45:26,030
Did you sleep well
at Eun Bin's last night?

770
00:45:27,300 --> 00:45:30,570
Eun Bin and I talked all night,
so I only got three hours of sleep.

771
00:45:31,230 --> 00:45:32,370
Eun Bin's a lot of fun, isn't she?

772
00:45:32,940 --> 00:45:35,500
Yes, she seems like
a really lovely person.

773
00:45:35,940 --> 00:45:36,940
Yes.

774
00:45:41,880 --> 00:45:43,110
So, why aren't you two dating?

775
00:45:44,750 --> 00:45:45,750
What?

776
00:45:45,810 --> 00:45:49,120
It seems to me
that you like her, too.

777
00:45:51,890 --> 00:45:54,360
Eun Bin's just like
a little sister to me.

778
00:45:54,760 --> 00:45:56,630
I've known her since she was little,

779
00:45:57,130 --> 00:45:58,360
and we know each other really well.

780
00:46:01,130 --> 00:46:03,130
So you've never seen her
as more than a friend?

781
00:46:04,100 --> 00:46:06,140
Right. And Eun Bin knows that, too.

782
00:46:07,440 --> 00:46:09,170
I don't think
that's how she sees it.

783
00:46:09,970 --> 00:46:10,970
What?

784
00:46:12,170 --> 00:46:14,140
From what I can tell,

785
00:46:14,740 --> 00:46:16,950
I don't think you know
your own heart yet.

786
00:47:09,230 --> 00:47:12,070
This stop is Onjeong Intersection.

787
00:47:12,730 --> 00:47:15,300
The next stop is Cheongri Villa.

788
00:47:27,320 --> 00:47:28,380
(Onjeong Intersection)

789
00:47:28,450 --> 00:47:30,720
What are you doing here?
When did you get on?

790
00:47:31,320 --> 00:47:32,750
In front of the office.

791
00:47:34,120 --> 00:47:36,960
Don't tell me you followed me.

792
00:47:38,060 --> 00:47:39,060
No.

793
00:47:39,600 --> 00:47:42,130
My father got hurt,
so I'm heading to my parents' house.

794
00:47:43,170 --> 00:47:46,540
Then why are you taking the bus
instead of driving?

795
00:47:49,070 --> 00:47:51,670
I'm tired and was afraid
I'd doze off at the wheel.

796
00:47:52,140 --> 00:47:53,480
Plus, I might have a drink.

797
00:47:56,250 --> 00:47:57,480
I see.

798
00:47:58,310 --> 00:48:00,480
Well, get home safe.

799
00:48:01,080 --> 00:48:02,120
Yes.

800
00:48:44,060 --> 00:48:46,090
I thought you said
you'd give me time to think.

801
00:48:46,860 --> 00:48:48,060
So why are you doing this?

802
00:48:49,430 --> 00:48:50,530
Go on and think.

803
00:48:51,100 --> 00:48:53,900
It's not like I'm distracting you,
is it?

804
00:48:55,640 --> 00:48:58,870
Then, why do you keep following me?

805
00:48:59,710 --> 00:49:01,610
I told you.
I'm going to my parents' place.

806
00:49:01,910 --> 00:49:03,880
It's not this way.

807
00:49:06,320 --> 00:49:08,680
Fine. I followed you
because I was worried.

808
00:49:09,150 --> 00:49:10,650
There was that incident nearby,

809
00:49:10,650 --> 00:49:12,020
and it's unsafe
to walk alone at night.

810
00:49:12,150 --> 00:49:13,160
Happy now?

811
00:49:13,220 --> 00:49:16,630
That's why you took the bus?

812
00:49:17,930 --> 00:49:18,930
Yes.

813
00:49:19,330 --> 00:49:21,530
You would've just said no
if I offered to drive you home.

814
00:49:25,630 --> 00:49:27,140
Go on.

815
00:49:27,770 --> 00:49:29,340
I'll leave
after I see you get inside safely.

816
00:50:12,510 --> 00:50:13,780
Where is it?

817
00:50:16,550 --> 00:50:18,390
- Uncle.
- Hey.

818
00:50:18,450 --> 00:50:19,450
What are you doing out here?

819
00:50:20,620 --> 00:50:22,190
I think I threw something out
by mistake.

820
00:50:23,160 --> 00:50:24,160
What was it?

821
00:50:24,990 --> 00:50:27,100
- Shampoo.
- Shampoo?

822
00:50:27,160 --> 00:50:29,970
Yes, shampoo.
It's my absolute favorite.

823
00:50:34,940 --> 00:50:35,940
Found it.

824
00:50:37,610 --> 00:50:38,610
I found it.

825
00:50:40,710 --> 00:50:41,710
I found it!

826
00:50:48,550 --> 00:50:49,620
Me. I like you.

827
00:50:51,120 --> 00:50:52,290
I'm the one who worries about you.

828
00:50:53,220 --> 00:50:54,460
I'm the one who misses you.

829
00:50:58,190 --> 00:50:59,460
I like you. A lot.

830
00:51:02,330 --> 00:51:03,330
Mom.

831
00:51:03,670 --> 00:51:04,900
You're home.

832
00:51:05,870 --> 00:51:07,000
Are you really mad at me?

833
00:51:07,670 --> 00:51:10,210
Why would I be mad?
I was just worried.

834
00:51:14,210 --> 00:51:15,280
I'm sorry, Mom.

835
00:51:15,580 --> 00:51:19,410
My gosh, what's this?
Wow, it's so beautiful.

836
00:51:20,020 --> 00:51:21,250
I heard somewhere...

837
00:51:21,780 --> 00:51:23,290
that women love getting flowers.

838
00:51:24,450 --> 00:51:26,020
It's true. I do love flowers.

839
00:51:26,420 --> 00:51:28,960
This is the first time
anyone's ever given me flowers.

840
00:51:29,520 --> 00:51:30,560
Thank you, son.

841
00:51:33,430 --> 00:51:34,760
It smells wonderful.

842
00:51:37,130 --> 00:51:38,130
There.

843
00:51:38,630 --> 00:51:42,070
All done.
You should worry about yourself.

844
00:51:42,140 --> 00:51:44,010
Why are you fussing over me?

845
00:51:44,010 --> 00:51:45,670
Come on.
Once "Human Theater" starts,

846
00:51:45,740 --> 00:51:49,010
you'll be on camera a lot,
so you need to look pretty.

847
00:51:49,340 --> 00:51:52,280
- Not that you aren't beautiful.
- Stop.

848
00:51:52,710 --> 00:51:54,750
- Do you want to do it, too?
- No.

849
00:51:55,580 --> 00:52:00,220
- I have a hypothetical question.
- Okay. What is it?

850
00:52:01,190 --> 00:52:04,730
Let's say you love a guy so much
you want to be with him forever,

851
00:52:05,060 --> 00:52:07,630
but his mom is kind of the worst.
What do you do?

852
00:52:08,600 --> 00:52:10,900
I thought you said
Jun Hyeok doesn't have any family.

853
00:52:11,370 --> 00:52:14,270
No, it's not about me.
I'm asking for a friend.

854
00:52:14,470 --> 00:52:17,870
She asked me for advice,
and I didn't know what to say.

855
00:52:18,270 --> 00:52:20,880
What exactly is so bad
about his mother?

856
00:52:21,340 --> 00:52:25,310
Apparently, she'd do anything
for her family.

857
00:52:25,710 --> 00:52:28,280
And she's the type who doesn't care
who gets hurt in the process.

858
00:52:29,580 --> 00:52:31,290
That sounds a lot like
someone we know.

859
00:52:32,690 --> 00:52:34,990
It's not anyone you two would know.

860
00:52:35,490 --> 00:52:37,060
Just give me some advice.

861
00:52:38,330 --> 00:52:42,730
Such devotion often comes from
deep anxiety and a need for control.

862
00:52:43,030 --> 00:52:47,340
Someone like that will likely demand
the same from her daughter-in-law.

863
00:52:47,840 --> 00:52:50,240
I'd tell her absolutely not.

864
00:52:51,970 --> 00:52:54,140
- What about you, Grandma?
- I'm against it, too.

865
00:52:55,040 --> 00:52:56,780
But the guy is absolutely perfect.

866
00:52:57,310 --> 00:53:00,650
If their love is strong enough,
can't they overcome it?

867
00:53:01,020 --> 00:53:03,420
Honey, marriage isn't...

868
00:53:03,490 --> 00:53:06,020
just about the two of them
being happy together.

869
00:53:07,120 --> 00:53:10,730
But what if they live on their own?
They don't have to see her, right?

870
00:53:10,860 --> 00:53:12,230
Even if you don't live together,

871
00:53:12,590 --> 00:53:14,630
there are always so many
family functions and obligations.

872
00:53:15,500 --> 00:53:18,300
You have no idea how many patients
at my clinic...

873
00:53:18,500 --> 00:53:22,800
suffer from stress and depression
because of their mothers-in-law.

874
00:53:43,390 --> 00:53:46,800
- What?
- You're injured, so don't drink.

875
00:53:47,830 --> 00:53:48,830
What? Why not?

876
00:53:49,700 --> 00:53:50,900
What are you here
to grill me about now?

877
00:53:51,400 --> 00:53:53,870
Why did you take that knife
for Dr. Gong?

878
00:53:54,440 --> 00:53:55,900
You've always been a coward.

879
00:53:58,110 --> 00:53:59,140
No, don't...

880
00:54:00,240 --> 00:54:01,280
It was just... In that moment,

881
00:54:02,110 --> 00:54:03,450
I just reacted without thinking.

882
00:54:06,150 --> 00:54:07,150
What?

883
00:54:07,620 --> 00:54:09,020
Are you suggesting
I did it on purpose?

884
00:54:11,690 --> 00:54:12,690
You really...

885
00:54:13,560 --> 00:54:15,520
You really see me as a total jerk,
don't you?

886
00:54:18,690 --> 00:54:20,760
You haven't told Dr. Gong yet,
have you?

887
00:54:23,200 --> 00:54:25,430
I'm going to,
so stop nagging me about it.

888
00:54:27,070 --> 00:54:28,200
Don't tell him.

889
00:54:32,140 --> 00:54:33,140
What?

890
00:54:35,140 --> 00:54:37,680
That's what Ju Ah wants.

891
00:54:39,580 --> 00:54:40,580
Really?

892
00:54:41,850 --> 00:54:42,880
Yes.

893
00:54:45,690 --> 00:54:46,720
Thanks.

894
00:54:48,190 --> 00:54:49,220
Thanks a lot.

895
00:54:49,990 --> 00:54:51,730
You don't have me to thank for it.

896
00:54:52,230 --> 00:54:54,000
It was Ju Ah's decision.

897
00:55:00,900 --> 00:55:03,610
My gosh. Did Hyun Bin really
tell you not to say anything?

898
00:55:04,070 --> 00:55:06,710
Yes. It was Jeong Han's daughter.

899
00:55:07,310 --> 00:55:09,540
Ju Ah said she didn't want us
to tell him.

900
00:55:10,610 --> 00:55:13,720
Oh, my. Honey, that's such a relief.

901
00:55:14,520 --> 00:55:15,550
I know.

902
00:55:16,280 --> 00:55:18,520
I feel guilty saying it,
but I'm so happy.

903
00:55:20,420 --> 00:55:21,890
Does that make me a hypocrite?

904
00:55:22,790 --> 00:55:23,930
Am I a terrible person?

905
00:55:24,860 --> 00:55:27,500
Anyone would feel that way.
Don't be so hard on yourself.

906
00:55:28,700 --> 00:55:29,700
You think so?

907
00:55:31,430 --> 00:55:33,940
(Taehan)

908
00:55:49,920 --> 00:55:53,920
Can I stay in the Design Office
until I've figured things out?

909
00:56:01,360 --> 00:56:03,230
I thought you were staying
in the Design Office...

910
00:56:03,230 --> 00:56:04,900
until you figured things out.

911
00:56:05,470 --> 00:56:06,700
I've figured it out.

912
00:56:09,840 --> 00:56:12,740
Do you want to get lunch
with me today?

913
00:56:14,410 --> 00:56:16,580
I made a reservation
at an Argentinian restaurant.

914
00:56:22,750 --> 00:56:23,820
Here you go.

915
00:56:24,350 --> 00:56:27,560
Dong Ik, you should eat
plenty of meat. Here.

916
00:56:28,790 --> 00:56:30,930
Hey, you didn't have to
treat me to a meal.

917
00:56:31,130 --> 00:56:34,460
You've always loved hot pot.
I heard this place was good.

918
00:56:34,760 --> 00:56:36,060
I'm not complaining.

919
00:56:36,900 --> 00:56:39,570
By the way, wasn't there something
you wanted to tell me?

920
00:56:40,470 --> 00:56:43,070
- What?
- The day you got hurt,

921
00:56:43,510 --> 00:56:46,140
things were so hectic
that I completely forgot about it.

922
00:56:46,740 --> 00:56:48,480
That. I was just...

923
00:56:48,910 --> 00:56:50,980
I was just feeling restless
with the show about to air...

924
00:56:51,480 --> 00:56:53,250
and wanted to grab a drink with you,
that's all.

925
00:56:55,080 --> 00:56:56,720
Gosh, you got me all worked up
over nothing.

926
00:56:59,920 --> 00:57:02,720
- It's the "Human Theater" writer.
- Oh, you should take it. Quick.

927
00:57:04,230 --> 00:57:06,230
Yes, hello. Yes.

928
00:57:07,130 --> 00:57:10,670
That's right. It slipped my mind.
Yes, I'll send it over right away.

929
00:57:11,970 --> 00:57:14,170
Shoot, the video of our duet...

930
00:57:14,400 --> 00:57:17,270
I kept forgetting to ask Eun Bin
to send it to me.

931
00:57:17,910 --> 00:57:20,710
Really? Hey, send that to me, too.

932
00:57:20,710 --> 00:57:24,310
Sure, I'll send it to the writer,
and then forward it to you.

933
00:57:24,380 --> 00:57:25,610
Sounds good.

934
00:57:26,280 --> 00:57:28,520
- By the way, Dong Ik.
- Yes?

935
00:57:28,650 --> 00:57:32,520
I managed to arrange a get-together
with Councilor Hwang this weekend.

936
00:57:33,020 --> 00:57:34,520
- Really?
- Yes.

937
00:57:34,820 --> 00:57:37,460
Hey, could you book
a nice restaurant for us?

938
00:57:37,830 --> 00:57:40,060
You know I have no clue
about high-end places.

939
00:57:40,230 --> 00:57:42,230
Sure, no problem. I'll find a place.

940
00:57:43,160 --> 00:57:46,940
- Thanks, man.
- What for? I should thank you.

941
00:57:47,440 --> 00:57:49,640
Hey, Dong Ik. Speaking of which...

942
00:57:50,210 --> 00:57:52,270
You did save my life once, you know.

943
00:57:52,810 --> 00:57:55,640
I'm going to grant you one wish.

944
00:57:56,380 --> 00:58:00,950
- A wish?
- Yes. Be careful what you wish for.

945
00:58:01,520 --> 00:58:03,520
Because no matter what it is,
I'll make it happen.

946
00:58:04,690 --> 00:58:05,690
Okay.

947
00:58:06,820 --> 00:58:09,090
Man, I've been talking too much.
Let's eat.

948
00:58:09,160 --> 00:58:11,160
- Okay. Let's eat.
- Eat up. You need your strength.

949
00:58:16,800 --> 00:58:17,800
Here.

950
00:58:20,400 --> 00:58:24,370
- This is an empanada.
- I know.

951
00:58:24,870 --> 00:58:26,670
It's a classic Argentinian snack.

952
00:58:29,110 --> 00:58:32,110
I studied all about it because
I was planning to cook for you.

953
00:58:36,280 --> 00:58:37,290
Next time...

954
00:58:40,720 --> 00:58:42,220
I'll make them for you.

955
00:58:47,400 --> 00:58:50,130
Does this mean you forgive me?

956
00:58:51,230 --> 00:58:52,230
Yes.

957
00:58:59,240 --> 00:59:02,010
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic,
Onjeong Market)

958
00:59:02,610 --> 00:59:06,550
Okay, this will help reduce oiliness
on your scalp.

959
00:59:06,710 --> 00:59:11,650
It's a detoxifying herbal treatment.
About your hair's growth cycle...

960
00:59:12,750 --> 00:59:13,890
One moment.

961
00:59:15,990 --> 00:59:19,830
It's Eun Bin's video.
I'm so sorry. This is urgent.

962
00:59:19,890 --> 00:59:21,560
Let me just forward this,
and I'll be right with you.

963
00:59:22,630 --> 00:59:25,200
Darn it. I can't see this thing.

964
00:59:26,170 --> 00:59:28,270
Looks like you're starting
to need reading glasses, too.

965
00:59:28,370 --> 00:59:30,610
That ship sailed a long time ago.

966
00:59:30,670 --> 00:59:32,170
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

967
00:59:37,810 --> 00:59:39,980
Where is that thing? Seriously...

968
00:59:40,980 --> 00:59:42,350
Goodness!

969
00:59:42,720 --> 00:59:45,590
I left it here and looked all over.
Gosh, I swear.

970
00:59:49,020 --> 00:59:50,020
What?

971
00:59:50,590 --> 00:59:53,590
What's this?
Dong Ik sent me a video?

972
00:59:55,230 --> 00:59:57,800
And now, the greatest duet
in all of Onjeong Market.

973
00:59:57,870 --> 01:00:00,270
Shall we have a listen?

974
01:00:00,700 --> 01:00:03,640
<i>We live on through love</i>

975
01:00:07,740 --> 01:00:09,580
(I'll see you later, Jeong Han.)

976
01:00:18,320 --> 01:00:19,320
What the...

977
01:00:19,720 --> 01:00:22,460
(Korean Medicine Doctor
Yang Dong Ik)

978
01:00:22,520 --> 01:00:25,130
What on earth did I just send?

979
01:00:32,100 --> 01:00:35,540
What is this? That little punk!
Did he send this by mistake?

980
01:00:43,440 --> 01:00:44,450
This is...

981
01:00:45,080 --> 01:00:49,420
Wait a minute.
Wait, isn't this the same video...

982
01:00:50,180 --> 01:00:51,690
that was on YouTube?

983
01:00:58,860 --> 01:00:59,860
Jeong Han.

984
01:01:00,900 --> 01:01:02,160
Did you see the video?

985
01:01:03,200 --> 01:01:08,040
- You set all this up, didn't you?
- What?

986
01:01:09,640 --> 01:01:12,110
Posting that video
of your wife falling...

987
01:01:13,070 --> 01:01:14,810
and getting my Ju Ah disciplined...

988
01:01:15,640 --> 01:01:16,840
That was you?

989
01:01:18,010 --> 01:01:19,010
Jeong Han.

990
01:01:51,810 --> 01:01:54,420
(Recipe For Love)

991
01:01:55,880 --> 01:01:58,890
- Do you have a girlfriend?
- She has a child.

992
01:02:01,660 --> 01:02:04,230
He's like a real brother to me now.

993
01:02:04,330 --> 01:02:06,790
- Hello.
- We're practically family.

994
01:02:10,060 --> 01:02:11,900
That scent...
I've smelled it somewhere before.

995
01:02:12,500 --> 01:02:16,140
You're so pretty when you smile.
Like a fresh head of lettuce.

996
01:02:17,270 --> 01:02:18,270
Lettuce?

997
01:02:18,510 --> 01:02:22,010
I never give up on what I like,
no matter what anyone says.

998
01:02:22,280 --> 01:02:23,510
Ju Ah was the one
who said to drop it.

999
01:02:23,580 --> 01:02:27,250
Now that Dad knows,
the whole family will find out.

1000
01:02:27,320 --> 01:02:29,850
Please, keep the rest of the family
from finding out.
